Therefore, the Override Flag must be set as to what the problem is. o X May not be set by any user or online application. o Any application setting override reason to X must get prior approval from the FUSION group o Future batch address ZIP+4 maintenance allowed. o Future NCOA allowed.</xs:documentation> </xs:annotation> </xs:enumeration> <xs:enumeration value="Y"> <xs:annotation> <xs:documentation>Override was set previously in CHEERS, and no reason is available. o blank stored in OVERRIDE-PROBLEM. o No update in FUSION can use Y as a reason. Any address update will require a 'valid' override value listed above, if the new address is to be overridden. o This will be for historical purposes only, to better gauge which Override reason is used the most. o Neither ZIP+4 nor NCOA maintenance allowed. o Some of these may be converted during migration to FUSION.</xs:documentation> </xs:annotation> </xs:enumeration> <xs:enumeration value="N"> <xs:annotation> <xs:documentation>Not overridden.
